      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DHAULAGIRI NZ (6) won two back at Kapunda from a nice gate. Drew a wide gate last start and was safely held, beaten 5.5 metres into fourth at Mt Gambier over 2190m. This looks a sterner test than last time but on his best form he is capable of a far better performance. PEACE OF HEAVEN NZ (1) could only manage to finish seventh at his latest appearance over 2050m at Port Pirie, a poor reflection on his short quote. Form prior to that was far better, including a win over 1800m at this track two starts ago. Has the benefit of a good draw and he is good enough to play a major role. LORD ZARIAS NZ (11) is next in line and although he has to contend with an awkward gate a win is not out of the question. BELLEZZA NERA (5) has been about the mark of late and must be respected, the latest offering a sound third at Kapunda over 2610m.",
